Build the new example site "__NAME__" in this repository (hwaro-examples).

The manifest entry for "__NAME__" already exists in manifest.json — it is your
complete art-direction assignment (category, scheme, palette, typography,
layout, signature, content plan). Do not modify manifest.json.

MANDATORY reading order, before creating any file:
1. The "__NAME__" entry in manifest.json.
2. DESIGN.md — all of it. §15 is your step-by-step process; §16 is your final
   checklist.
3. AGENTS.md — especially "Template pattern library" and "Idioms that build
   green but render broken".
4. The hwaro-design skill appended at the end of this prompt (upstream,
   loaded fresh each run) — it is the authoritative reference for how design
   lives in a Hwaro site (tokens, CSS delivery, motion, the Section 9 anti-
   slop tells, the Section 12 pre-flight check). DESIGN.md/AGENTS.md still
   govern this collection's own process and template idioms; on a
   collection-specific rule the two disagree on, DESIGN.md wins.

Build rules (non-negotiable):
- Create examples/__NAME__ ONLY via `cd examples && hwaro init __NAME__`. Never
  copy, move, rename, or modify any other directory under examples/ — other
  examples are read-only reference material. If examples/__NAME__ already
  exists before you scaffold, STOP and report instead of reusing anything.
- Follow DESIGN.md §15 in order: scaffold fresh, design tokens first, then
  templates, then the signature element, then content.
- Copy ALL template logic from the AGENTS.md pattern library. Do not invent
  template idioms. If the site is `auto`-scheme: include the pre-paint theme
  guard and theme.js exactly as the library shows, define both palettes per
  DESIGN.md §6, and override the code-block background with palette tokens
  (highlight themes are single-scheme).
- The homepage has exactly one <h1>, on the first screen, in the display font.
- The signature element must be visible on the homepage's first screen
  (1280x720). Budget your band heights: everything above the signature's
  bottom edge must sum to under 720px. Show this arithmetic in your report.
- Prose is centered or paired with real matter — never a 65ch column pinned
  left inside a wide container with a permanently empty right half.
- Content per DESIGN.md §12: real fictional prose, 150+ PROSE words per page
  (front matter, code fences, and shortcode calls do not count), dates spread
  across 2025-01..2026-06, real tags, <!-- more --> markers on listable pages.
- No emoji, no lorem ipsum, no binary assets, no external origins beyond
  Google Fonts and cdn.jsdelivr.net, all CSS in static/css/style.css, every
  href through {{ base_url }}.
- If something renders empty or a build fails, check the broken-idioms table
  in AGENTS.md before trying anything else.

Verification (do not report success without all of these):
1. DESIGN.md §15 step 9: build + all four rendered-output greps (including
   `grep -c '<h1' public/index.html` == 1) + manually confirm the home listing
   shows real titles, dates, and links.
2. DESIGN.md §16 design QA pass: every checkbox. For first-screen items,
   show the band-height arithmetic — do not certify from source reasoning.
3. `scripts/check-site.sh __NAME__` must print "PASS: __NAME__".
4. Run `scripts/sync-tags.sh`, then inside examples/__NAME__ run
   `hwaro tool agents-md --remote --write --force` (the --force matters:
   hwaro init already created AGENTS.md, and without it hwaro blocks on an
   interactive overwrite prompt).

Final report format:
- check-site.sh output, verbatim
- the four grep commands and their outputs
- the first-screen height budget arithmetic
- the §16 checklist with every item marked [x] and one line of concrete
  evidence each (a command output or file:line — not just "yes")

Do NOT git commit anything. Leave all changes in the working tree for review.

